               <msContents>
                  <summary>Part of the "Book of the Names of All Things" (vol. i): the companion
                     volume to <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_582">F. 16
                        (BBF. 9)</ref>, corresponding to it in size, hand, and arrangement, covering
                     (incompletely) Váḥids ii-vii (Váḥid i is missing, though a statement of its
                     contents is prefixed to the index).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_17-item1">
                     <note>Vol. 1</note>
                     <author key="person_9878408" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9878408/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Bāb, ʻAlī Muḥammad Shīrāzī, 1819-1850</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="person_9878408">the Bāb</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">باب، ميرزا علي محمد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1861">Min kitāb asmāʼ kull shayʼ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_1861">من كتاب اسماء كل شيء</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc">Book of the Names of All Things (vol. i)</title>
                     <note>A colophon in red ink (f. 91b) dates this volume to Safar 4, AH 1304
                        (<date when="1886-11-02">2 November 1886</date>) - Browne notes this is
                        "nearly a year and a half" after the companion second volume (BBF. 9).</note>
                     <note>Includes a table of contents listing the "Names" commentated in each
                        Váḥid, and a further list of marginal annotations specifying occasions or
                        addressees for several chapters, including one naming Mírzá Aḥmad Kátib as
                        scribe for part of the work.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">(table of contents, Váḥid i
                        onward)</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" defective="true"/>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/87">p.61</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBF. 10</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts (Continuation)", in Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Oct., 1892): 637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations">Apparently the companion volume of the Bāb's <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Kitāb al-asmāʼ <foreign xml:lang="ar">كتاب الاسماء</foreign>
                           </title>, which bears the classmark <idno>F. 16</idno>.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
